{"title_page": "Hina Altaf (actress)", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Hina Altaf Khan\n| image              = \n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| native_name        =  \n| native_name_lang   = \n| pronunciation      = \n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1992|01|02}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dailypakistan.com.pk/15-Sep-2018/848349|title=\u067e\u0627\u06a9\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646\u06cc \u0627\u062f\u0627\u06a9\u0627\u0631\u06c1 \u062d\u0646\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0637\u0627\u0641 \u06a9\u06cc \u06a9\u0644\u0627\u0626\u06cc \u067e\u0631 \u0645\u0648\u062c\u0648\u062f \u06cc\u06c1 \u2019\u0679\u06cc\u0679\u0648 \u2018 \u062a\u0648 \u0622\u067e \u0646\u06d2 \u062f\u06cc\u06a9\u06be\u0627 \u06c1\u0648 \u06af\u0627 \u0645\u06af\u0631 \u06cc\u06c1 \u06a9\u0633 \u0644\u0691\u06a9\u06d2 \u06a9\u0627 \u0646\u0627\u0645 \u06c1\u06d2 \u0627\u0648\u0631 \u0648\u06c1 \u06a9\u0648\u0646 \u06c1\u06d2 \u061f \u067e\u06c1\u0644\u06cc \u0645\u0631\u062a\u0628\u06c1 \u0631\u0627\u0632 \u0633\u06d2 \u067e\u0631\u062f\u06c1 \u0627\u0679\u06be\u0627 \u062f\u06cc\u0627|date=2018-09-15|website=[[Daily Pakistan]]|language=en|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref>\n| birth_place        = [[Karachi]], [[Sindh]], Pakistan\n| nationality        = Pakistani\n| other_names        = \n| citizenship        = \n| home_town          = \n| education          = \n| alma_mater         = [[Iqra University]]\n| occupation         = Actress\n| years_active       = 2014\u2013present\n| relatives          = \n| spouse             = \n| partner            = \n| height             =\n| weight             = \n| awards             = \n| website            =\n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      = \n}}\n'''Hina Altaf Khan''' is a Pakistani actress, television presenter and former video jockey who works in the [[Pakistani dramas|Urdu dramas]]. A majority of her series has been produced by [[MD Productions|Momina Duraid Productions]] for [[Hum TV]] channel. Khan in known for portraying supporting to leading roles in several television series, and has become a popular celebrity in the country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.brecorder.com/2018/12/17/459580/hina-altaf-lashes-out-over-hype-about-aamir-liaquats-second-marriage/|title=Hina Altaf lashes out over hype about Aamir Liaquat\u2019s second marriage|date=2018-12-17|website=[[Business Recorder]]|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://arynews.tv/en/hina-altaf-driver-birthday-instagram/|title=People 'salute' Hina Altaf over sweet gesture on Instagram|date=2019-01-04|website=[[ARY News]]|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.magtheweekly.com/detail/1044-hina-altaf|title=HINA ALTAF {{!}} Cover Story|website=Mag - The Weekly|language=en|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.brecorder.com/2018/03/19/405811/pakistani-actress-hina-altafs-fans-arent-happy-with-her-bold-photo-shoot/|title=Pakistani actress Hina Altaf\u2019s fans aren\u2019t happy with her \u2018bold\u2019 photo shoot|last=says|first=Kam|date=2018-03-19|website=[[Business Recorder]]|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref><ref name=hina1>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/magazine/instep-today/121633-Televisions-new-faces-that-deserve-our-attention|title=Television\u2019s new faces that deserve our attention|last=Shabbir|first=Buraq|website=[[The News International]]|language=en|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref> \n\nAltaf made her television debut with a supporting role in the [[ARY Digital]]'s melodrama ''[[ARY Digital|Maryam Kese Jiye]]'' in 2015. She subsequently starred as the titular character in the 2015 romance ''[[Ek Thi Misaal]]'', and gained wider recognition for playing a rape victim in the highly successful social drama ''[[Udaari]]'' (2016), which ranks among the [[Pakistani dramas|highest-rated Urdu dramas of all time]]. Altaf has since played leading roles in several television series, including the the romantic series ''[[Dil-e-Jaanam (2017 TV series)|Dil-e-Jaanam]]'' (2017), ''[[Gumrah (TV series)|Gumrah]]'' (2017), ''[[Pagli (TV series)|Pagli]]'' (2017), ''[[Aatish (series)|Aatish]]'' (2018) and ''[[Dil-e-Gumshuda|Dil-e-Gumshuda]]'' (2019). Altaf co-host the fourth season of the musical show ''[[Pepsi Battle of the Bands|Battle of the Bands)]]'' along with actor [[Ali Safina]] in 2019.<ref name=pepsi>{{Cite web|url=https://dailytimes.com.pk/429642/ali-safina-joins-hina-altaf-as-host-for-battle-of-the-bands-season-2s-new-episode/|title=Ali Safina joins Hina Altaf as host for 'Battle of the Bands' Season 2's new episode|date=2019-07-13|website=[[Daily Times (Pakistan)|Daily Times]]|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-17}}</ref> Khan started her own [[YouTube]] channel in 2019, where she regularly uploads vlogs and behind the scene videos of her shoots.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://galaxylollywood.com/2019/05/30/here-is-what-your-favorite-celebrities-are-up-to-on-their-youtube-channels/|title=Here is what your favorite celebrities are up to, on their YouTube channels|last=Batool|first=Maisooma|date=2019-05-30|website=Galaxy Lollywood|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-20}}</ref>\n\n==Television==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Director !! Channel !! Notes !! Ref(s).\n|-\n| 2015 || ''Maryam Kasay Jeeya ''|| Maryam || Syed Atif Hussain || [[ARY Digital]] || || <ref name=hina1/>\n|-\n| 2015 || ''[[Judaai (TV series)|Judaai]]'' || Amariya || Syed Ramish Rizvi || [[Geo TV]] || || <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oyeyeah.com/entertainment/new-faces-who-took-over-pakistani-showbiz-in-2018/|title=New Faces Took Over Pakistani Showbiz in 2018|date=2019-01-09|website=Oyeyeah|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015 || ''[[Madventures (Pakistani game show)|Madventures (season 2)]]'' || Contestant || Khurram Farid || ARY Digital || || <ref>{{C