18|date=2019-01-09|website=Oyeyeah|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2018 || ''[[Aatish (series)|Aatish]]'' || Asma || Saima Waseem || Hum TV || || <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dailytimes.com.pk/345641/would-love-triumph-over-family-politics/|title=Would love triumph over family politics?|date=2019-01-18|website=[[Daily Times (Pakistan)|Daily Times]]|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019 || ''[[Pepsi Battle of the Bands|Battle of the Bands (season 4)]]'' || Host || Andrew Bramley || Geo TV || || <ref name=pepsi/>\n|-\n| 2019 || ''[[Dil-e-Gumshuda]]'' || Zara || Shaqielle Khan || Geo TV || || <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/magazine/instep-today/444631-amar-khan-will-be-seen-as-a-fierce-woman-in-her-next|title=Amar Khan will be seen as a fierce woman in her next|last=NewsBytes|website=[[The News International]]|language=en|access-date=2019-03-30}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2020 || ''Rabba Menu Maaf Karin'' || Zoya || Kashif Zaman || Hum TV || || <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oyeyeah.com/entertainment/new-faces-who-took-over-pakistani-showbiz-in-2018/|title=New Faces Took Over Pakistani Showbiz in 2018|date=2019-01-09|website=Oyeyeah|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2020 || ''[[Bandhay Aik Dor Say]]'' || TBA || Ali Faizan || Geo TV || || <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/magazine/instep-today/573807-upcoming-tv-dramas-to-look-out-for|title=Upcoming TV dramas to look out for|last=Shirazi|first=Maria|website=www.thenews.com.pk|language=en|access-date=2020-02-15}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{imdbname|nm10097667}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Pakistani female models]]\n[[Category:Pakistani television actresses]]\n[[Category:People from Karachi]]\n[[Category:Iqra University alumni]]\n[[Category:Pakistani YouTubers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Hina Altaf\n| image              = \n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| native_name        =  \n| native_name_lang   = \n| pronunciation      = \n| birth_name         = Hina Altaf Khan\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1992|01|02}}\n| birth_place        = [[Karachi]], [[Sindh, Pakistan]]\n| nationality        = [[Pakistan]]\n| other_names        = \n| citizenship        = \n| home_town          = \n| education          = \n| alma_mater         = [[Iqra University]]\n| occupation         = [[Actress]], VJ, host\n| years_active       = 2014 \u2013 Present\n| relatives          = \n| spouse             = \n| partner            = \n| height             =\n| weight             = \n| awards             = \n| website            =\n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      = \n}}\n'''Hina Altaf''' also known as '''Hina Altaf Khan''' is a Pakistani television actress, VJ and host. She made her television debut with a leading role of Maryam in the serial ''Maryam Kese Jiye''. Then, she appeared as Misaal in ''[[Ek Thi Misaal]]''. After that, she was seen portraying lead roles in ''[[Aik Thi Misaal|Ek Thi Misaal]]'', ''[[Udaari]]'', ''[[Dil-e-Jaanam (2017 TV series)|Dil-e-Jaanam]]'', ''[[Pagli (TV series)|Pagli]]'', ''[[Gumrah (TV series)|Gumrah]],'' ''[[Aatish (series)|Aatish]]'' and ''[[Dil-e-Gumshuda|Dil-e-Gumshuda.]]''\n\nIn 2019, Khan co-host [[Pepsi]]'s ''[[Pepsi Battle of the Bands|Battle of the Bands (season 4)]]'' along with actor [[Ali Safina]].<ref name=pepsi>{{Cite web|url=https://dailytimes.com.pk/429642/ali-safina-joins-hina-altaf-as-host-for-battle-of-the-bands-season-2s-new-episode/|title=Ali Safina joins Hina Altaf as host for 'Battle of the Bands' Season 2's new episode|date=2019-07-13|website=[[Daily Times (Pakistan)|Daily Times]]|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-17}}</ref> She has established herself as one of the leading actresses in Pakistani television.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.brecorder.com/2018/12/17/459580/hina-altaf-lashes-out-over-hype-about-aamir-liaquats-second-marriage/|title=Hina Altaf lashes out over hype about Aamir Liaquat\u2019s second marriage|date=2018-12-17|website=[[Business Recorder]]|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://arynews.tv/en/hina-altaf-driver-birthday-instagram/|title=People 'salute' Hina Altaf over sweet gesture on Instagram|date=2019-01-04|website=[[ARY News]]|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.magtheweekly.com/detail/1044-hina-altaf|title=HINA ALTAF {{!}} Cover Story|website=Mag - The Weekly|language=en|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.brecorder.com/2018/03/19/405811/pakistani-actress-hina-altafs-fans-arent-happy-with-her-bold-photo-shoot/|title=Pakistani actress Hina Altaf\u2019s fans aren\u2019t happy with her \u2018bold\u2019 photo shoot|last=says|first=Kam|date=2018-03-19|website=[[Business Recorder]]|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref><ref name=hina1>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/magazine/instep-today/121633-Televisions-new-faces-that-deserve-our-attention|title=Television\u2019s new faces that deserve our attention|last=Shabbir|first=Buraq|website=[[The News International]]|language=en|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dailypakistan.com.pk/15-Sep-2018/848349|title=\u067e\u0627\u06a9\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646\u06cc \u0627\u062f\u0627\u06a9\u0627\u0631\u06c1 \u062d\u0646\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0637\u0627\u0641 \u06a9\u06cc \u06a9\u0644\u0627\u0626\u06cc \u067e\u0631 \u0645\u0648\u062c\u0648\u062f \u06cc\u06c1 \u2019\u0679\u06cc\u0679\u0648 \u2018 \u062a\u0648 \u0622\u067e \u0646\u06d2 \u062f\u06cc\u06a9\u06be\u0627 \u06c1\u0648 \u06af\u0627 \u0645\u06af\u0631 \u06cc\u06c1 \u06a9\u0633 \u0644\u0691\u06a9\u06d2 \u06a9\u0627 \u0646\u0627\u0645 \u06c1\u06d2 \u0627\u0648\u0631 \u0648\u06c1 \u06a9\u0648\u0646 \u06c1\u06d2 \u061f \u067e\u06c1\u0644\u06cc \u0645\u0631\u062a\u0628\u06c1 \u0631\u0627\u0632 \u0633\u06d2 \u067e\u0631\u062f\u06c1 \u0627\u0679\u06be\u0627 \u062f\u06cc\u0627|date=2018-09-15|website=[[Daily Pakistan]]|language=en|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref> Khan started her own [[YouTube|Youtube]] channel in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://galaxylollywood.com/2019/05/30/here-is-what-your-favorite-celebrities-are-up-to-on-their-youtube-channels/|title=Here is what your favorite celebrities are up to, on their YouTube channels|last=Batool|first=Maisooma|date=2019-05-30|website=Galaxy Lollywood|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-20}}</ref>\n\n==Television==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year!! Title!! Role!!Notes!!Refs\n|-\n| 2015 || ''Maryam Kasay Jeeya ''|| ||  ||<ref name=hina1/>\n|-\n| 2015 ||''[[Judaai (TV series)|Judaai]]'' || Amariya ||  ||\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[Madventures (Pakistani game show)|Madventures (season 2)]]''\n|Contestant\n|\n|\n|-\n| 2016 ||''[[Ek Thi Misaal]]''|| Misaal|| ||<ref name=hina1/>\n|-\n| 2016 ||''[[Karb]]''|| Eman (young) ||  ||\n|-\n| 2016 ||''[[Abro (TV serial)|Abro]]''||Afsheen || ||<ref name=hina1/>\n|-\n| 2016 ||''[[Udaari]]''|| Zebo || ||<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/magazine/instep-today/148473-Redefining-TVs-regressive-narrative|title=Redefining TV\u2019s regressive narrative|last=Isani|first=Aamna Haider|website=[[The News International]]|language=en|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://images.dawn.com/news/1176161|title=&#39;Main victim nahi, survivor hoon&#39;: Udaari delivers its most important message yet|last=Haider|first=Sadaf|date=2016-09-01|website=[[Dawn (newspaper)|DAWN]]|language=en|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2016 ||''[[Natak]]''|| Sabeen ||  ||\n|-\n| 2016 ||''[[Saya-e-Dewar Bhi Nahi]] ''|| Aainoor|| ||\n|-\n| 2017 ||''[[Kuch Na Kaho (TV series)|Kuch Na Kaho ]]''|| Rania|| ||<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oyeyeah.com/entertainment/new-faces-who-took-over-pakistani-showbiz-in-2018/|title=New Faces Took Over Pakistani Showbiz in 2018|date=2